<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Delete Your Data - BuildOnBudget</title>
  <link href="/output.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link href="/toast.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/images/logo.png" type="image/x-icon">
</head>

<body class="w-full bg-bg-primary text-text-primary min-h-screen flex flex-col">
  <div class="flex-grow py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-accent mb-2">Delete Your Data</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">How to remove your account and associated data</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">How to Delete Your Data</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Deleting your account is the only step needed to remove all your data from our servers. When you delete your account, we immediately remove:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li>Your profile information</li>
            <li>All your projects and project data</li>
            <li>Budget information</li>
            <li>Task lists</li>
            <li>Any other data associated with your account</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">No Separate Request Needed</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Because we delete all associated data immediately when you delete your account, you do not need to send a separate data deletion request. Once your account is deleted, all your data is permanently removed from our servers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">How to Delete Your Account</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
            To delete your account:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li>Log in to your BuildOnBudget account</li>
            <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> in the app</li>
            <li>Click the <strong>Delete Account</strong> button</li>
            <li>Confirm the deletion when prompted</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">What Happens After Deletion</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Once you confirm account deletion, your account and all associated data are permanently and immediately removed from our servers. This action cannot be undone.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            If you have any questions about deleting your data, contact us at support@buildonbudget.com.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div class="pt-4">
          <a href="/privacy" class="inline-flex items-center text-accent hover:underline">
            &larr; Back to Privacy Policy
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="bg-bg-secondary text-text-secondary py-4 mt-auto border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4">
      <p class="text-sm">&copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> BuildOnBudget. All rights reserved.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <a href="/terms" class="text-sm hover:text-accent transition">Terms of Service</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="text-sm hover:text-accent transition">Privacy Policy</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>

</html>
